cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as word sense disambiguation. The use of bidirectional long short-term memory networks also suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) or "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the fact that the model is trained end-to-end and makes effective use of word order suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the evaluation of the approach on standard datasets suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval).
